{"id": 1720, "title": "Ticket #1720: condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() fails on Mac OS X 10.4", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe failure of the lib_auth_config test on the trunk (and 7.5.4 branch) that is consistently happening under x86_macos_10.4 appears to be caused by the ipv6 changes.\n\n<p>In condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6(), if I add the following line, things work:\n\n</p><p></p><div class=\"verbatim\">\n<pre>sinaddr.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Without the above line, getnameinfo() returns EAI_FAMILY under OS X 10.4.  My laptop (OS X 10.5) works without the above line, even when running the same binary that fails under OS X 10.4.\n\n</p><p>Not all platforms even have a sin_len member of sockaddr_in.  Apparently this is a 4.4BSD thing.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Dec-27 11:26</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/f23fa40a17f5936498d16bf35133b3cabae9a5d9\">[19793]</a></span>: Fix regression in condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() affecting OS X 10.4. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1720\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1720'); return false;\" title=\"condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() fails on Mac OS X 10.4\">#1720</a></span> The cmake merge resulted in HAVE_STRUCT_SOCKADDR_IN_SIN_LEN never being defined.  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Oct-20 09:50</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/a2a9d21e73d0b5dfb456612b90e8f27ea133bb9f\">[25744]</a></span>: Document hostname authentication bug on mac 10.4 <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1720\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1720'); return false;\" title=\"condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() fails on Mac OS X 10.4\">#1720</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Oct-19 16:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1646d7f03ca3c872ba54534ba17af4197db0e2aa\">[25738]</a></span>: Documented fix for condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6(). <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1720\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1720'); return false;\" title=\"condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() fails on Mac OS X 10.4\">#1720</a></span>  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Oct-19 16:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/8b9c5580b6a8d15e7679918f027adb50592c1656\">[19187]</a></span>: Fix for condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() on Mac OS X 10.4. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1720\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1720'); return false;\" title=\"condor_gethostbyaddr_ipv6() fails on Mac OS X 10.4\">#1720</a></span>  (By Dan Bradley )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2010-Oct-19 17:00", "status": "resolved", "created": "2010-Oct-19 16:15", "fixed_version": "2010-Oct-19 16:15", "broken_version": "v070504", "priority": "4", "subsystem"